games.comment: Doug Baldwin. Speaking of Baldwin, the undrafted rookie hauled in 4 grabs for 83 yards and a touchdown, though most of his yardage came on a somewhat fluky 55-yard, 4.h-quarter score. Ignore him in fantasy leagues.    I found it hilarious that Seahawk fans on GameCenter posted comments at halftime like, T-Jack needs to step up, we can't rely on Marshawn! At that time, Lynch had just 6 yards on 7 carries. Ladies and gentlemen, Seattle's 2011 offense! Lynch finished with 33 yards on 13 attempts, by the way.

Doug Baldwin caught it and ran toward the end zone for a 54-yard gain. The Seahawks scored a touchdown on the next play. Wilson finished 22-of-32 for 238 yards and 2 touchdowns. Wilson was under pressure more than he anticipated because of Brown's injury. Brown was supposed to provide some stability up front for the Seahawks, but once he left the game, the Seahawks reverted to their previous state where Wilson is constantly hounded and needs to make some amazing plays to give his team a chance to win.
